{"lemma":"عِلّاتٌ","slug":"عِلّاتٌ","root":"ع.ل.ل","root_slug":"ع-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30117","n30130","n30131"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%84%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"second draught of a drink"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"co-wife, wife other than the first wife (in polygamy)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"defect, vice"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"disease, malady, bug"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"defect, irregularity","tags":["especially"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"defect, weakness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the transition from one metrical foot to another"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cause, reason"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"excuse, pretext, apology, plea"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕal.la/","/ʕil.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30117","headword_ar":"عَلَّهُ","root":"El","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalalN","text_ar":"عَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~N","text_ar":"عَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him to drink the second time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEl~hu","text_ar":"اعلّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEolaAlN","text_ar":"اـِعْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also 2 and 4.] ―         -b2-  [Hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dyed it a second time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a hide: see a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHolifN","text_ar":"مُحْلِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  Hence [also], (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~a AlD~aAribu","text_ar":"عَلَّ الضَّارِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaDoruwba","text_ar":"المَضْرُوبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beater plied the beaten with a continued beating;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~ahu","text_ar":"عَلَّهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobFA","text_ar":"ضَرْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaTaA='u A@ll~`hi muDaAEafN yaEul~u bihi","text_ar":"عَطَا=ءُ ا@للّٰهِ مُضَاعَفٌ يَعُلُّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAdahu mar~apF baEoda A^uxoraY","text_ar":"عِبَادَهُ مَرَّةً بَعْدَ اُخْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The gift of God is redoubled; He bestows it upon his servants one time after another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~a","text_ar":"عَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~a binafosihi","text_ar":"عَلَّ بِنَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the verb being also intrans., (S, O,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,) inf. ns. as above, (TK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drank"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, * S, O, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second draught:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, * S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drank after drinking, uninterruptedly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~ati AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"عَلَّتِ الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels drank the second draught."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA TaEaAmN qadN","text_ar":"هٰذَا طَعَامٌ قَدٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~a minohu","text_ar":"عُلَّ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is food of which some has been eaten."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, K. *)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~a","text_ar":"عَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~N","text_ar":"عَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, IAar, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, diseased, sick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ill;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Msb, K;) and (Msb, K) so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtl~","text_ar":"اعتلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotilaAlN","text_ar":"اِعْتِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~a","text_ar":"عُلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the pass. form:       -A5-  and the trans. verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~ahu","text_ar":"عَلَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEl~hu","text_ar":"اعلّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor. in this case"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb. See 4.)       -A6-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~a Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"عُلَّ الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned in the S, with the addition ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahuwa maEoluwlN","text_ar":"فَهُوَ مَعْلُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but without any explanation; perhaps as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing was caused;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~apN","text_ar":"عِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ a cause, ” of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoluwlN","text_ar":"مَعْلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.) is the correlative: but the context seems to indicate that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing was used for the purpose of diverting from some want:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Golius appears to have read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~a","text_ar":"عَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and to have been led by what next precedes it in the S to render it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loco alterius rei fuit lactavitve res."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA","IAar","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n30130","headword_ar":"عَلَّةٌ","root":"El","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"second draught."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (Mgh,) A woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fellow-wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"her"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband's wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, * K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a step-mother:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the former is the more correct meaning: (Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aAtN","text_ar":"عَلَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) Whence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw AlEal~aAti","text_ar":"بَنُو العَلَّاتِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sons of one father by different mothers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though, when he added by marriage a second wife to the first, he took a second draught. (S, * Mgh, O, * Msb, * K. *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awolaAdu AlA^axoyaAfi","text_ar":"اَوْلَادُ الاَخْيَافِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the contr. of this: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awolaAdu AlA^aEoyaAni","text_ar":"اَوْلَادُ الاَعْيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the sons of the same father and mother. (Msb.) Accord. to IB, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA A^axawaAni mino Dar~atayoni","text_ar":"هُمَا اَخَوَانِ مِنْ ضَرَّتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[They two are brothers from two fellow-wives]; but they did not say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino Dar~apK","text_ar":"مِنْ ضَرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and accord. to ISh, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo banuw Eal~apK","text_ar":"هُمْ بَنُو عَلَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awolaAdu Eal~apK","text_ar":"اَوْلَادُ عَلَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anobiyaA='u banuw Eal~aAti","text_ar":"الاَنْبِيَا=ءُ بَنُو عَلَّاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awolaAdu Eal~aAtK","text_ar":"اَوْلَادُ عَلَّاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The prophets are of different mothers, but of one religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one faith, but of different religious laws"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordinances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EulaAlapN","text_ar":"عُلَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","TA","T"]},{"entry_id":"n30131","headword_ar":"عِلَّةٌ","root":"El","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An accident that befalls an object and causes its state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, to become altered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A disease, sickness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malady;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;) because, by its befalling, the state becomes altered from strength to weakness; so says El-Munáwee in the “ Tow- keef: ” (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disease that diverts"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the ordinary occupations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. regarded as being from what next follows]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilalN","text_ar":"عِلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~aAtN","text_ar":"عِلَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An accident,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, that diverts the person to whom it occurs from his course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the object of his want:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) as though it became a second occupation hindering him from his former occupation. (S, O.) ―         -b4-  And [hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an excuse; an apology; a plea whereby one excuses himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence, (K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAtaEodamu xaroqaA='u Eil~apF","text_ar":"لَاتَعْدَمُ خَرْقَا=ءُ عِلَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrq","text_ar":"خرق"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) [See also another ex. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sA^l","text_ar":"سال"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 3.] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cause:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an efficient cause:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M, K:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Eil~apN lih`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا عِلَّةٌ لِهٰذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a cause of this:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Eil~atuhu","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ عِلَّتُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is its cause:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~apN wamaEoluwlN","text_ar":"عِلَّةٌ وَمَعْلُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cause and effect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a phrase of frequent occurrence in theological and other works:] and [sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eil~apN","text_ar":"عِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pretext,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pretence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] it is said in a trad. of 'Áïsheh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fakaAna Eabodu Alr~aHom`ni yaDoribu rijoliY","text_ar":"فَكَانَ عَبْدُ الرَّحْمٰنِ يَضْرِبُ رِجْلِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEil~api Alr~aAHilapi","text_ar":"بِعِلَّةِ الرَّاحِلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And 'Abd-Er-Rahmán was beating my leg with the pretence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pretext, of"},{"kind":"text","text":"his beating the side of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"with his leg. (TA.) ―         -b6-  The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Eil~aAtihi","text_ar":"عَلَى عِلَّاتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In every case."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) Zubeyr says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_in~a Albaxiyla maluwmN Hayovu kaAna waA`\n                      \n                     \n                        kin~a AljawaAda EalaY Eil~aAtihi harimu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the niggard is blamed wherever he be; but the liberal in all his circumstances is Herim"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O:) meaning his companion Herim Ibn-Sinán El-Murree. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hrm","text_ar":"هرم"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","S","O","K","M"]}]}}